{{nihongo|'''Takahiro Yamamoto'''|<U+5C71><U+672C> <U+9686><U+5F18>|extra=born [[July 12]], [[1978]]}} is a [[volleyball]] player from [[Japan]], who was one of the key players in the [[Japan men's national volleyball team|Men's National Team]] in the 2000s. 

Yamamoto plays as a wing-spiker and was named ''Best Scorer'' and ''Best Server'' at the [[2008 FIVB Men's World Olympic Qualification Tournaments|2008 Olympic Qualification Tournament]]. Yamamoto is renowned for his power, pace and exuberance. At 200cm and 87 kg he's one of the biggest players in the Japanese line-up.

==Honours==
*[[FIVB World League 2001|2001 FIVB World League]] &mdash; 9th place
*[[Volleyball Grand Champions Cup|2001 World Grand Champions Cup]] &mdash; 5th place
*[[FIVB World League 2002|2002 FIVB World League]] &mdash; 13th place
*[[2002 FIVB Men's World Championship|2002 World Championship]] &mdash; 9th place
*[[FIVB World League 2003|2003 FIVB World League]] &mdash; 13th place
*[[2003 FIVB Men's World Cup|2003 FIVB World Cup]] &mdash; 9th place
*[[FIVB World League 2004|2004 FIVB World League]] &mdash; 10th place
*[[2006 FIVB Men's World Championship|2006 World Championship]] &mdash; 8th place
* [[2008 FIVB Men's World Olympic Qualification Tournaments|2008 Olympic Qualification Tournament]] &mdash; 2nd place (qualified)

==Individual Awards==
* ''[[2003_FIVB_Men%27s_World_Cup#Awards|2003 FIVB World Cup "Most Valuable Player"]]''
* ''[[2003_FIVB_Men%27s_World_Cup#Awards|2003 FIVB World Cup "Best Scorer"]]''

